Step 1: Identify the accounts to include:
• Cash on Hand = 2,067,352.98
• Bank Deposits = 3,752,082.80
• Interest Receivable = 12,737.96
• Accounts Receivable = 321,015.98

Step 2: Compute the total quick assets:
Total Quick Assets = 2,067,352.98 + 3,752,082.80 + 12,737.96 + 321,015.98 = 6,153,189.72

Step 3: Identify the current liabilities (end amount):
Total Current Liabilities = 7,605,149.91

Step 4: Calculate the Quick Ratio:
Quick Ratio = Total Quick Assets / Total Current Liabilities = 6,153,189.72 / 7,605,149.91 ≈ 0.81

Thus, the answer is:

{"solution": {"Quick Ratio": "0.81"}}
